Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise); slice into 1⁄2-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Pat @pork filet{10%oz}(dry with paper towels) dry with paper towels; season all over with half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add pork and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss zucchini with a drizzle of cooking oil, salt, and pepper on opposite side of baking sheet with pork.

Roast on top rack until pork is cooked through and zucchini is lightly browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

When pasta has 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of cooking oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add tomato and garlic; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water, @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

Add drained spaghetti, zucchini, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, a splash of reserved pasta cooking water, and a drizzle of @olive oil{} to pan with sauce; toss to combine.

> If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide spaghetti between plates; top with pork and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.